cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with game-theoretic aspects of sequential interdiction settings, which suggests that it could belong to cs.GT (Game Theory). The paper also involves designing algorithms and exploring computational complexity, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), respectively. The use of network structures and feedback mechanisms could suggest cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as another possible category. Finally, the paper involves strategic decision-making by both the interdictor and the evader, which could suggest cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible category.
